<p class="mainhead">Christian Education Volunteer Opportunities</p>
<% end %>

<p><strong>Adult Forum Leaders</strong> plan and host discussions or videotape forums for adults on topics including Christian teachings and social concerns.</p>
<p><strong>Church Library Volunteers</strong> catalog, shelve and check books, videotapes, magazines and related materials.</p>
<p><strong>Holiday Program Assistants</strong> help with holiday pageants, musical performances, crafts and activities for the Sunday School children as needed.</p>
<p><strong>Lenten Program Assistants</strong> help with five weekly Lenten Soup Night dinners as needed.  Volunteers serve on a team, which is responsible for preparing food, setting up tables in Parish Hall, serving and clean up after the dinner.</p>
<p><strong>Sunday School Teachers and Substitutes</strong> review course materials, plan, and teach a class of children, age four through grade six, about our faith.  <strong>Sunday School Helpers</strong> assist the teachers with lessons or activities.</p>
<p><strong>Vacation Bible School Teachers</strong> provide a Christian education program for children from three years old through fourth grade, half-days for one week in the summer.  <strong>Vacation Bible School Assistants</strong> assist the teachers and volunteers with lessons, crafts, music, drama and recreation.  A <strong>Crafts Coordinator</strong> plans, purchases material for, and implements creative activities for Vacation Bible School.  A <strong>Recreation Coordinator</strong> plans and supervises a recreation program for the Bible School students.  A <strong>Snack Coordinator</strong> plans, purchases, and serves themed snacks for the children.</p>
